                <note rend="inline" type="source">860p.512 Residence/7: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Latvia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Sussdorff</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Riga</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-11-21T16:00:00+02:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 21, 1928—4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received November 21—11:15 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>94. Would appreciate an immediate telegraphic reply to my urgent despatch No.
                    5601 of October 3rd, submitting proposal which would eliminate residence tax on
                    American citizens in Latvia. Consulate reports that failure to settle the matter
                    is causing serious inconvenience to American citizens here.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Sussdorff</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
